the house has approved legislation to bring 
the united states into line with an international agreement to 
combat illegal trafficking in african elephant ivory 
the measure sent to the senate by voice vote on monday would 
prohibit imports into this country of any ivory taken in violation 
of the convention on international trade in endangered species 
that worldwide agreement uses a system of quotas and ivory 
markings in an effort to regulate the international trade in ivory 
from african elephants whose numbers have fallen to an estimated 
700000 from 15 million in 1979 
the bill would ban importation of raw ivory from any nation 
without a native elephant population and would prohibit exportation 
of raw ivory from the united states 
