<TEXT>
the crowded skies above ohare international 
airport and basic errors by its air traffic controllers have 
prompted federal aviation officials to scrutinize operations at the 
worlds secondbusiest airport 
the national transportation safety board on monday called for a 
backtobasics training program for traffic controllers at 
ohare to counter an unusually high number of controller errors 
federal aviation administration officials say they also plan a 
broad review of operations at ohare 
after a special investigation the ntsb recommended that 
controllers at ohare be provided with new and better equipment and 
that the faa find ways to increase controller staffing reduce peak 
traffic loads improve training and develop better quality 
assurance 
the faa declined to comment directly on the recommendations but 
