egypt and israel ended talks tuesday without 
reaching a compromise solution to a border dispute over taba a 
resort area on the aqaba gulf claimed by both countries officials 
said 
there has been no agreement on any of the subjects discussed 
during the daylong talks said nabil araby head of egypts 
delegation to an international arbitration body in geneva that is 
to settle the dispute over the 250acre area 
no further talks are planned and the israeli delegation was 
scheduled to fly home later in the day foreign ministry officials 
said 
taba which israel captured in its 1967 war with egypt was not 
returned after the 1979 peace treaty the two countries in 1986 
agreed to accept a final decision on the territory by a fivemember 
international panel in geneva the result of the arbitration is 
expected in september 
the united states mediated tuesdays talks held at a hotel near 
the giza pyramids on the outskirts of cairo 
the delegations in tuesdays negotiations were led by yossi ben 
aharon israeli prime minister yitzhak shamirs chief aide ahmed 
maher director of the egyptian foreign ministrys legal 
department and abraham sofaer legal adviser to the us state 
department 
it was the fourth meeting between israel and egypt on the issue 
a previous session held in washington in june also failed to 
resolve the differences 
egyptian foreign minister esmat abdelmeguid told reporters 
tuesday that egypt considers taba part of its territory and hopes 
to win its case in geneva in recent weeks egyptian officials 
including president hosni mubarak have emphasized that their 
countrys sovereignty over taba was not negotiable 
taba has a hotel and a tourist village both israeliowned and 
egypt has offered to buy them 
ben aharon in an aug 1 interview with newsweek magazine said 
that egypt and israel should either divide the territory or make 
it a neutral zone and give both sides equal rights 
maher warned in an interview published monday in the cairo 
newspaper alahram that if the israeli side brought up such a 
suggestion during tuesdays talks this would signal the end of 
the meeting 
