operation of a countervigilante group in violation of the 
constitutional rights of the first group 
to tolerate a rape of the rights of the klan would be a 
recognition that some sort of double standard exists for the 
application of constitutional protections he said 
the government appealed and the 11th circuit ruled that the 
testimony should not be suppressed 
the 11th circuit ordered ackers removal from the case when the 
government filed a second appeal arguing that he had failed to 
follow the circuit courts directions 
