three men with shotguns and pistols 
entered a hospital room and killed a patient and his bodyguard in 
what appeared to be drugrelated murders police reported tuesday 
police cmdr ivan catala said the men wore hoods entered the 
bayamon regional hospital in suburban san juan through the morgue 
at about 10 pm monday killed the victims and escaped 
he identified the slain men as herminio torres quiles 33 who 
had been hospitalized for a bullet wound in the stomach and his 
bodyguard angel m rosario 30 
catala said drug charges were pending against torres and 
detectives believed the killings were linked to trafficking 
torres was wounded july 20 in a gunfight between two groups of 
people at a housing project in bayamon and his companions fled 
leaving him behind in a car police found a pistol and a small 
quantity of drugs in the car according to catala 
he said torres would not cooperate with investigators and 
refused police protection saying he had his own laws for 
dealing with enemies 
