<TEXT>
defense minister dmitri t yazov says the soviet 
union must fight complacency in the ranks and delays in new weapons 
programs if it is to keep other countries from gaining military 
superiority 
in an article published tuesday yazov recommended ambitious 
action to cleanse the military of outdated attitudes improve the 
reliability of military hardware and make the human factor 
dominant in the soviet military 
yazovs article in the defense ministry newspaper red star was 
an unusually frank account of problems in the soviet military 
before mikhail s gorbachev began his policy of glasnost or 
openness the military was presented only as strong and 
problemfree 
the defense minister has spoken candidly of the militarys 
problems since he was appointed in may 1987 the 64yearold army 
genera was quoted as saying in a speech three months ago that 
soviet soldiers in east germany lack discipline and battle 
readiness 
his latest comments encompassed the entire soviet armed forces 
our military thought is still partially constrained by 
inertia routine and a lack of competition of ideas and opinions 
he wrote 
he said the gap must be reduced between theoretical research on 
new weapons and their actual development and deployment and 
oversimplification and showiness must be removed from military 
training 
bureaucracy and a tendency to blame problems on others plagues 
the soviet armed forces at all levels yazov declared he said 
young commanders soldiers and officers take a passive attitude 
toward deficiences 
senior officers must not alienate themselves from those they 
command he wrote and all ideological and political upbringing 
must be built so that the person is always in the center of 
attention 
yazov said the goal should not be accumulation of military 
might of the armed forces but maintenance of the might at a 
level that precludes military superiority over us and guarantees a 
reliable defense 
last week yazov toured soviet military facilities with frank 
carlucci the visiting us defense secretary 
</TEXT>
