joy elektra teddy pendergrass 
 
joy is a steamy set of soul songs that never overheats due 
to the restraint of the tempos arrangements and teddy pendergrass 
delivery 
even when pendergrass sings of explosions of ecstacy flowing 
from you and me on 2 am his cooing manner is such that 
the words would probably slip right past tipper gore 
the song titles can we be lovers im ready love is 
the power show that pendergrass is obsessed with the same thing 
as prince but pendergrass is less overt 
the accompaniment steers clear of lead guitars or horns that 
would clash with pendergrass smooth style drums bass and 
lowprofile keyboards dominate the closest thing to a frill is 
three female backup singers pendergrass plays off them when he 
raps briefly enough to avoid being corny and when he improvises 
nicely on the chorus of through the falling rain 
the eight love songs on joy are all played at midtempo 
pendergrass message is clear this is music for romancing not 
dancing 
by steven wine associated press writer 
