walmart stores incs said tuesday its profits soared 34 
percent in the second quarter while limited inc which remained 
mired in the yearold apparel industry slump said its earnings 
dropped 46 percent 
walmart has been one of the few standouts in the struggling 
retail industry the discount store chain said it earned 1796 
million or 32 cents a share in the quarter ended july 31 up from 
1341 million or 24 cents a share a year earlier 
the companys sales increased in the latest quarter to 485 
billion from 373 billion 
retail sales have fallen off over the past year in part because 
of womens disenchantment with fashions but also because consumers 
have been trying to pay down their installment debt levels 
industry analysts say walmart consistently outperforms other 
retailers because of its competitive pricing the company also has 
an efficient cost structure enabling it to turn a large profit 
limited said its secondquarter earnings totaled 307 million 
or 17 cents a share down from 572 million or 30 cents a share 
in the same 1987 period 
the apparel retailers sales reached 8931 million during the 
quarter up from 8221 million 
limited chairman leslie h wexner said the company anticipated 
relatively poor results and had kept its inventories at 1987 levels 
and controlled the markdowns that have eroded apparel retailers 
earnings for a year 
industry analysts believe the retailers will see signs of a 
recovery in the third quarter 
