<TEXT>
investment banker drexel burnham lambert inc 
will buy the commodities brokerage business of staley continental 
inc for an undisclosed amount the companies said tuesday 
the sale of staley commodities international inc marks the 
second divestment of a major staley asset since early june when 
londonbased sugar refiner tate amp lyle plc completed its 15 
billion acquisition of the rolling meadows illbased company 
tate amp lyle said when it set out to buy staley that it would 
keep only staleys corn syrup refining business the secondlargest 
such operation in the nation tate amp lyle sold staleys 
foodservice business to sysco corp for 700 million in june 
staley established staley commodities in 1976 to handle its own 
commodity brokerage requirements the brokerage has since grown to 
become a member of the chicago board of trade with 26 seats on 
various commodity exchanges 
the sale agreement calls for new yorkbased drexel to transact 
for at least two years the agricultural hedging operations 
previously handled by staley commodities 
staley also agreed to drop a 1987 lawsuit alleging that drexel 
had tried to extort staleys management into a takeover and had 
manipulated staleys stock to thwart a stock offering 
drexel had denied the allegations 
drexel officials said in a statement that the acquisition of 
staley commodities was an important addition to drexels commercial 
grain futures brokerage business one of the countrys largest 
staley commodities account executives will be invited to join 
drexel the companies said 
